               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18340220-184-person1743">
                  THOMAS 
                  GOODYEAR
               <interp inst="t18340220-184-person1743" type="surname" value="GOODYEAR"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-184-person1743" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-184-person1743" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             (police-constable, E 39). I saw the prisoners on the 1st of February, in Oxford-market - I followed them down Oxford-street, as far as Hanway-street - I saw Kelly turn round and say, "Piper," - meaning that I was watching them - when he said that, he went across the road - then Mills went down Charles-street, towards Soho-square - I found that they were parting - I ran and seized him - I found on him one pint pot - I then snatched hold of his collar, and run him down Oxford-street, where I overtook Kelly - I put him into a tobacconist's shop - I found three pots on him - Mills has a pocket made on purpose for pot stealing all round him.</p>
               <p>JAMES ALEHOUSE. I <rs id="t18340220-184-viclabel1050" type="occupation">keep the <placeName id="t18340220-184-crimeloc1051">Edinburgh Castle, in Welbeck-street</placeName>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-184-crimeloc1051" type="placeName" value="Edinburgh Castle, in Welbeck-street"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18340220-184-crimeloc1051" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                     <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18340220-184-off1048 t18340220-184-crimeloc1051"></join>
                  </rs> - this pewter pot is mine; it is worth about 1s. 3d. - it was found on Mills - I have lost five dozen within the last five months.</p>
